The article highlights the increase in domestic violence during the COVID-19 pandemic, referring to it as a "shadow pandemic" of violence. It emphasizes that women from underserved and marginalized communities are disproportionately affected. The author emphasizes the importance of ending gender-based violence, stating that it is both a moral and strategic imperative. The author mentions their own efforts in addressing this issue, including the establishment of the Gender Policy Council and the plan to issue the first National Action Plan to End Gender-Based Violence. The article concludes by emphasizing the need to prioritize the elimination of violence against women and create a culture that refuses to tolerate abuse.